cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata in this file."
title: "Autonomous Physics Lab"
abstract: >-
  Autonomous Physics Lab is a verification-first scientific engine for
  generating, testing, simulating, falsifying, scoring, and reusing physics
  hypotheses through deterministic code and version-controlled scientific
  memory. It is the first physics proof-of-work for Open Agent Science. It is a
  hypothesis-testing and benchmarking system, not a source of automatic
  discoveries.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Hladun
    given-names: Roman
  - name: "Autonomous Physics Lab contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/gladunrv/autonomous-physics-lab"
url: "https://github.com/gladunrv/autonomous-physics-lab"
license: MIT
version: "0.1.0"
keywords:
  - open agent science
  - physics
  - hypothesis testing
  - falsification
  - reproducibility
  - benchmark
  - formula discovery
  - scientific memory
